'County Donegal' ( or ; or Contae ThÃ­r Chonaill) is a county in Ireland. It
is part of the Border Region and is also located in the province of Ulster.
It is named after the town of Donegal. Donegal County Council is the local
authority for the county. The population of the county is 161,137 according
to the 2011 census.
